  <h2><a href="../../blog-posts/worldwatch-report-green-economy-and-green-jobs-china" title="Worldwatch Report: Green Economy and Green Jobs in China">Worldwatch Report: Green Economy and Green Jobs in China</a></h2>

      <span class="submitted">Posted by Worldwatch Institute on Aug 19, 2011</span>
  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <div class="field field-type-filefield field-field-image">
    <div class="field-items">
            <div class="field-item odd">
                    <img src="../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/WorldWatch&#32;green&#32;jobs.jpg" alt="" title="" width="93" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/>        </div>
        </div>
</div>
<p>Aurthors  Dr. Jihua Pan, Haibing Ma, and Dr. Ying Zhang discuss the potential for China&#8217;s green development strategy to generate jobs in energy, transportation, and forestry in a <A href="http://www.worldwatch.org/node/8677">report</a> published by the <A href="http://www.worldwatch.org">Worldwatch Institute</a>.</p>

<blockquote><blockquote><blockquote>
<i>&#8220;Over the past decade, and especially during the 11th Five-Year period of 2006‚Äì10, China has prioritized green development in almost all of its leading economic sectors.</i></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote>
  </div>
<div class="clear-block">
    	<div class="readmore"> <a href="../../blog-posts/worldwatch-report-green-economy-and-green-jobs-china">Read more</a> </div>
  </div>

